Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with a cooperative D2D communication system, which involves networking and communication aspects. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a resource allocation scheme based on the optimal cooperation policy, which involves information theory concepts. 
3. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper formulates the pairing problem as a matching game, which involves game theory concepts. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a two-timescale resource allocation scheme, which involves control and optimization aspects. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with D2D communication, which can involve multimedia data transmission.
